# ============================================================
# BOT LONGS PROFESIONAL v1.1 — Variables de entorno LIMPIAS
# ============================================================

# API Keys BingX
BINGX_API_KEY=""
BINGX_API_SECRET=""

# Telegram
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=""
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=""

# --- Trading general ---
AUTO_TRADING_ENABLED="true"
MAX_OPEN_TRADES="2"
MAX_POSITION_SIZE="10"
MIN_TRADE_USDT="10"
FORCE_MIN_USDT="10.0"
LEVERAGE="3"
CHECK_INTERVAL="60"

# --- Scoring ---
MIN_SCORE="82"

# --- TP / SL ---
TAKE_PROFIT_PCT="2.5"
STOP_LOSS_PCT="1.5"

# --- Trailing Stop ---
TRAILING_STOP_ENABLED="true"
TRAILING_START_PCT="1.0"
TRAILING_LOCK_PCT="60"

# --- Protección de pérdidas ---
MAX_LOSS_PCT="5.0"

# --- Cooldowns ---
COOLDOWN_AFTER_TP_MIN="15"
COOLDOWN_AFTER_SL_MIN="45"

# --- Filtros de mercado ---
MIN_VOLUME_24H="500000"
MAX_SYMBOLS_TO_ANALYZE="50"
BTC_BEAR_BLOCK_PCT="1.5"

# --- Órdenes ---
USE_LIMIT_ORDERS="true"
SL_LIMIT_OFFSET_PCT="0.05"

# --- MAE / Patrones ---
MAE_PERIOD="20"
MAE_PCT="2.0"
PATTERN_SCORE="true"
REGIME_FILTER="true"
```

Los cambios clave son tres: `MAX_POSITION_SIZE`, `MIN_TRADE_USDT` y `FORCE_MIN_USDT` todos a **10**, sin duplicados, y eliminadas todas las variables del bot FLOOP que no usa este código (como `FLOOP_*`, `TP_ATR_MULT`, `ENABLE_SHORTS`, etc.) que pueden causar confusión.

Después de pegar esto en Railway, reinicia el servicio del bot de LONGS y verifica en los logs la línea:
```
[CONFIG] FORCE_MIN_USDT=10.0 | POSITION_SIZE=10.0 | MIN_TRADE=10.0
